args: Hee. Hee hee. Tee hee hee!\nTEEEEEE HEE HEE HEE HEEEE!
Er, Chelsea? Think you might be in the\nwrong room. Also how did you even get in?\nI'm pretty sure I locked the door.
Hah! As if some dumb lock could get\nbetween us.
...Sure. Well, I'm pretty beat, so if you\ndon't mind, could you like...leave, please?
How are we ever gonna get closer if\nyou keep pushing me away?!
Look, I wanna get some sleep, okay?!\nWe can hang out later.
I'll just stand guard here then. You get your\nbeauty sleep, and I'll be here aaaall night\nto make sure nobody disturbs you.

We've only known each other two weeks, for cryin'
out loud. There I was, goin' toe to toe with some
real tough fiends, when she showed up outta the
blue to save my butt.
Phew! That got kinda dicey for a second.\nThanks for the assist...Chelsea, was it?
Yup! And it was my pleasure.
Us meeting like this must be fate, huh?\nTee hee!
Uh, sure. You out here hunting fiends\nas well?
Wait, there's a sylvan village on\nthis mountain?
Nope! I live on my own in a little hut.\nLike a hermit! Tee hee!
With all these fiends around, it must be\npretty dangerous. You should think about\nmoving someplace safer.
Ohmigosh, you're worried about me?!\nEeeee! You are SO kind!
I don't know where I'd go, though.\nI don't have any family...
Why don't you come stay in our castle,\nthen?
W-wait, are you saying we should live\ntogether? In a CASTLE?!
Yeah! Everyone's welcome at the Halidom.
Plus, you're a heckuva shot with that bow.\nYou'd be great to have around!
This is all so sudden... I mean*gasp*!\nAre you propo...propos
So, whaddya think? Wanna come to the\ncastle with me?
Oh, YES! I DO! I do I do I doooo!
She seemed normal-ish at the time.\nBut once we got back to the castle...
Good work at training today, Luccy!\nI brought you a little pick-me-up.
Tee hee! I poured aaaaall my love\ninto it, just for you!
The eggs were laid just this morning,\nthe fish was caught at dawn, and the\nbread is still warm from the oven.
I even asked the butcher for his best cut\nof beef! And no, I totally did NOT spend\ntoo much time and/or money on this!
I want to give you everything I have,\nevery minute, of every day, FOREVER.\n'Cause you deserve it! Tee hee!
Dust dust dust, all day long!\nWipe wipe wipe, till it all shines!
Huh? Chelsea? What're you doing in\nmy room?
Cleaning it up nice and tidy, so you can\nenjoy every second you spend in it!
Uh, thanks, but I usually do that myself.\nI'm pretty particular about where all my\nstuff goes.
Oh, I know. I memorized all that\nDAYS ago.
By the way, you were up far too late\nlast night, mister!
Er, how did you know that?
While I was cleaning, I found hairs from\nyou, the prince, and Ranzal.

They weren't there when I came in to
clean after dinner last night, so that
MUST mean you three were up to
some late-night shenanigans!
Hold onhave you been cleaning my room\nevery day?
Of course, Luccy! It's part of my\ndaily routine.
Man, I'm wrecked. Time for a nice long\nsoak, I think.
Might have the bath to myself, even...\nWAAAAH! Chelsea?! Why are you\nfollowing me?!
Want me to wash your back for you?\nTee hee...

She just kept going, day after day after day.
I guess she wanted to repay me for bringing
her to the castle, but she's gone waaaay
overboard. I'm lookin' over my shoulder
constantly.
She said she'd wait till morning,\nbut there's no way she actually...
'Course! I didn't even fall asleep once.\nAre you proud of me?
Look, Chelsea. I don't really know how to\nput this gently, but...could you maybe\nback off a little?
I get that you're thankful, and you're\ndefinitely one of the most thoughtful\npeople I know. But there's a limit, yeah?
Oh, Luccy. You're such a jokester!\nI'm your WIFEthis is just what\nmarriage looks like!
When did you become my WIFE?!
When you invited me to live with you, silly!
I was SO happy you just up and proposed\nlike that.
Whoa, I did NOT propose to you!
Awww, you're embarrassed!\nYou're such a cutie-pie.
Ah! I need to get your breakfast started.\nSee you soon, my love! I'll miss youuuuu!
I gotta clear this up pronto...
Luca? What's with all the racket?
Oh, hey Sarisse. What're you doin' up\nso early?
The folks back home wanted to deliver an\nengagement gift. I just got back with it.
Oh yeah? Who's tyin' the knot?
Uh, you and your fiance, Chelsea.\nYou feeling okay?
